WEBVTT

00:00:07.170 --> 00:00:08.980
Satono Diamond Wins!

00:00:08.980 --> 00:00:14.740
Victory at the Hanshin Daishouten

00:00:09.550 --> 00:00:12.170
Looking flawless heading into
the Spring Tennoushou!

00:00:12.260 --> 00:00:14.740
Growing more and more polished, with her
sights set on the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe!

00:00:16.470 --> 00:00:17.740
Kitasan Black dominates the Osaka Hai!

00:00:17.740 --> 00:00:22.830
Kitasan Black Dominates

00:00:17.740 --> 00:00:22.830
4th G1 Win

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:20.640
An overwhelming victory
where no one else came close!

00:00:20.640 --> 00:00:22.830
The aura of a champion!

00:00:22.830 --> 00:00:24.950
Upsy-diddly-doo...

00:00:24.950 --> 00:00:28.250
Satono Diamond is building momentum
with her two G1 victories.

00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:32.570
And Kitasan Black has uncontested
credentials with four G1 wins.

00:00:32.570 --> 00:00:35.590
The two horse girls considered
to be the strongest around

00:00:35.590 --> 00:00:38.540
will be clashing once again
at the Spring Tennoushou!

00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:43.360
After Satono Diamond won at the Arima Kinen,
will Kitasan Black be able to get revenge?

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:46.570
Or will Satono Diamond's brilliance
be too bright to compare?

00:00:46.570 --> 00:00:49.320
Could we even see an upset by a dark horse?!

00:00:47.230 --> 00:00:52.230
No matter what, see the Spring Tennoushou!

00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:52.230
All eyes will be locked
on the Spring Tennoushou!

00:01:06.140 --> 00:01:07.080
Kita-chan...

00:01:07.480 --> 00:01:08.990
Are you up?

00:01:11.710 --> 00:01:13.360
Are you going somewhere?

00:01:16.590 --> 00:01:18.640
Let's go on a trip, Dia-chan.

00:01:38.410 --> 00:01:48.580
Umamusume

00:01:42.240 --> 00:01:48.580
Pretty Derby

00:02:52.020 --> 00:02:54.770
Fuchu Station

00:02:52.540 --> 00:02:56.550
Episode 9
Pushed by the Approaching Heat

00:02:54.770 --> 00:02:56.550
Snacks, check!

00:02:56.550 --> 00:02:58.030
Drinks, check!

00:02:58.030 --> 00:03:00.030
Tickets, check!

00:02:58.030 --> 00:03:00.030
18km Young Rider Ticket

00:03:01.100 --> 00:03:04.280
All set and ready to go!

00:03:04.780 --> 00:03:07.310
Okay, Dia-chan, where should we go?

00:03:07.310 --> 00:03:08.570
You didn't pick somewhere yet?

00:03:08.570 --> 00:03:11.280
I haven't! Should we go to the
mountains? Or maybe the beach?

00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:13.040
I think I like the mountains!

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:15.040
I'd like to see the ocean.

00:03:15.300 --> 00:03:16.800
Then let's play rock-paper-scissors for it!

00:03:17.270 --> 00:03:18.510
Okay.

00:03:18.510 --> 00:03:20.890
Rock, paper, scissors!

00:03:21.460 --> 00:03:23.180
To the beach it is.

00:03:41.050 --> 00:03:44.040
Okay, off to the ocean we go!

00:03:44.040 --> 00:03:45.660
Off we go!

00:03:49.130 --> 00:03:52.670
We haven't gone out like
this in a long time, huh?

00:03:53.640 --> 00:03:54.670
Look, the racecourse!

00:03:54.670 --> 00:03:57.420
Here

00:03:55.720 --> 00:03:57.420
There it is.

00:03:58.250 --> 00:04:00.340
We're heading out!

00:04:03.050 --> 00:04:04.290
Whatcha doing?

00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:06.890
I was wondering which
beach we should visit...

00:04:07.210 --> 00:04:08.560
Don't look it up!

00:04:09.110 --> 00:04:11.740
But wouldn't it be easier
to have a goal in mind?

00:04:11.740 --> 00:04:15.730
It'll be fine! As long as we're together,
we'll have a good time.

00:04:16.070 --> 00:04:19.730
And if I'm with you, I feel
like I could go anywhere!

00:04:20.390 --> 00:04:21.690
Kita-chan...

00:04:22.890 --> 00:04:24.240
Okay!

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:28.170
Then if we're not sure where to go next,
let's play rock-paper-scissors again.

00:04:28.170 --> 00:04:28.990
Yeah!

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:32.500
Here we are!

00:04:33.490 --> 00:04:36.000
Now, where should we go next?

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:38.090
I think I'll pick this.

00:04:38.750 --> 00:04:40.270
I pick this, then!

00:04:40.250 --> 00:04:41.260
Hokkaido

00:04:44.090 --> 00:04:46.510
Rock, paper, scissors!

00:04:49.760 --> 00:04:50.850
Come on, let's go!

00:07:47.230 --> 00:07:50.330
We've come pretty far, huh?

00:07:50.330 --> 00:07:51.220
Yeah.

00:07:51.860 --> 00:07:54.170
Where to next?

00:07:55.990 --> 00:07:57.100
Here!

00:07:55.990 --> 00:07:57.620
Isumi Lighthouse

00:08:17.770 --> 00:08:19.350
This is it!

00:08:22.830 --> 00:08:24.270
Wow...

00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:28.280
It's like you can see the whole planet.

00:08:28.680 --> 00:08:30.960
Yeah. It's beautiful.

00:08:32.320 --> 00:08:35.510
I don't think I've ever seen
a view like this before.

00:08:36.130 --> 00:08:38.130
Yeah. Me neither.

00:08:39.410 --> 00:08:43.700
Thanks for coming with me today, Dia-chan.

00:08:43.700 --> 00:08:49.420
You're welcome. It's been so long... I'm glad
we got to go on a trip like this again.

00:08:55.600 --> 00:09:00.200
So... you had something you
wanted to talk about, right?

00:09:01.220 --> 00:09:01.940
Yeah.

00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:11.950
I... y'know, I...

00:09:13.280 --> 00:09:15.300
I want to make everyone smile.

00:09:17.690 --> 00:09:23.370
Everyone who's been rooting for me all this
time. Everyone who's been looking out for me.

00:09:24.130 --> 00:09:30.170
The people who loudly encourage me.
The people who clap hard for me...

00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:33.660
Everyone I've disappointed.

00:09:34.350 --> 00:09:37.350
The ones who entrust me with
their dreams, in spite of that.

00:09:38.020 --> 00:09:39.850
People who don't even know me.

00:09:40.890 --> 00:09:43.600
Even people who are going to a
racecourse for the first time.

00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:48.320
I want them hyped up, excited, and smiling.

00:09:48.670 --> 00:09:51.400
I want my running to do that.

00:09:52.590 --> 00:09:53.450
So...

00:09:54.940 --> 00:09:56.780
I'm not going to lose again.

00:09:59.610 --> 00:10:04.770
I'm going to beat you at the
Spring Tennoushou, Satono Diamond.

00:10:10.890 --> 00:10:17.200
I wanted to be able to convey
the way I feel to you properly.

00:10:25.930 --> 00:10:26.940
I see.

00:10:32.940 --> 00:10:36.650
I have something I won't
compromise on, either.

00:10:38.140 --> 00:10:41.550
I'm going to win the Spring Tennoushou,
and then start racing overseas.

00:10:42.450 --> 00:10:47.080
So that I can achieve my dream of
winning the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:51.570
Which is why...

00:10:52.620 --> 00:10:54.460
I'll be the one who wins.

00:10:57.720 --> 00:10:58.970
Then let's race.

00:11:01.970 --> 00:11:05.970
Umamusume

00:11:01.970 --> 00:11:05.970
Pretty Derby

00:11:08.930 --> 00:11:12.940
An unending spring sky is
above us for this battle...

00:11:10.940 --> 00:11:12.940
Welcome to the Tokyo Racecourse!

00:11:13.610 --> 00:11:16.920
The biggest race of spring, which has
made its mark on history,

00:11:16.920 --> 00:11:18.380
and your memories, so many times...

00:11:18.850 --> 00:11:22.950
This race, this single
competition for victory...

00:11:23.410 --> 00:11:26.480
It's beginning soon. The Spring Tennoushou!

00:11:26.870 --> 00:11:28.410
And it's fair to say

00:11:28.410 --> 00:11:31.600
the spotlight will be on the battle
between Satono Diamond and Kitasan Black.

00:11:31.600 --> 00:11:35.300
At the previous Arima Kinen, it was
Satono Diamond who came out on top.

00:11:35.300 --> 00:11:38.690
That's true. And while we can look forward
to seeing them race in prime condition,

00:11:38.690 --> 00:11:40.010
given that this is the Tennoushou,

00:11:40.010 --> 00:11:42.880
I don't know if it's going
to be a simple one-on-one.

00:11:43.110 --> 00:11:44.330
Correct you are.

00:11:44.330 --> 00:11:47.690
And as for the racers looking to make their
presence felt in this duel between greats...

00:11:47.690 --> 00:11:51.810
Cheval Grand, who got third place
at the Japan Cup and previous Spring Tennoushou.

00:11:51.810 --> 00:11:54.900
She's become tangibly
stronger in the past year.

00:11:54.900 --> 00:11:56.900
This should be a really great race.

00:11:57.200 --> 00:11:59.400
Then there's the Satsukishou winner, Divinity.

00:11:59.710 --> 00:12:02.400
And the Grand Prix winner, All Haiyu.

00:12:02.770 --> 00:12:06.770
Will Satono Diamond be able to leave
these powerful competitors behind?

00:12:06.770 --> 00:12:09.710
She's felt a lot more solid
since winning the Arima Kinen.

00:12:09.710 --> 00:12:13.680
It's fair to say she's the horse girl
with the most momentum right now.

00:12:14.040 --> 00:12:17.620
Satono Diamond has made statements about
running in the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:12:17.620 --> 00:12:20.010
Will she win this race and
set the stage for that?

00:12:20.550 --> 00:12:25.300
And then we have Kitasan Black, who's
looking for revenge against Satono Diamond.

00:12:25.300 --> 00:12:27.120
She may have lost at the Arima Kinen,

00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:29.990
but those four G1 wins prove
she's a real contender.

00:12:29.990 --> 00:12:32.230
Her chance at revenge should
make for a great race.

00:12:32.210 --> 00:12:34.430
You can do it! You can do it, Kita-san!

00:12:32.230 --> 00:12:35.730
Wishes

00:12:34.430 --> 00:12:37.480
Get payback for the Arima Kinen!

00:12:37.480 --> 00:12:39.990
A clash of the titans
at the Spring Tennoushou.

00:12:39.990 --> 00:12:41.210
Takes you back, doesn't it?

00:12:41.210 --> 00:12:41.990
Yeah.

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:44.610
Mejiro McQueen versus Tokai Teio...

00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:46.910
The stage is set.

00:12:46.910 --> 00:12:48.420
The track is turf, and
it's condition is good.

00:12:48.420 --> 00:12:50.400
This battle to determine
the strongest horse girl...

00:12:50.400 --> 00:12:53.120
The Spring Tennoushou is about to begin!

00:12:59.420 --> 00:13:00.420
Victory so certain it was considered boring.

00:12:59.420 --> 00:13:01.500
McQueen is running! She's running!

00:13:01.500 --> 00:13:03.140
And she does it!

00:13:03.140 --> 00:13:05.820
For the first time in history, someone has
won the Spring Tennoushou twice in a row,

00:13:04.990 --> 00:13:07.430
Mejiro McQueen

00:13:05.820 --> 00:13:07.430
and it's Mejiro McQueen!

00:13:07.430 --> 00:13:08.430
A meteor glowing in the color of cherry blossoms

00:13:07.430 --> 00:13:09.860
Sakura Laurel is moving up! There she goes!

00:13:09.860 --> 00:13:11.670
Can she pass them?! She does!

00:13:11.670 --> 00:13:15.940
The cherry blossom is here! And
it's in full bloom! Sakura Laurel!

00:13:13.200 --> 00:13:15.940
Sakura Laurel

00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:16.940
A golden vessel on a journey to glory

00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:19.010
On the outside, we can see Maiden Charm!
But Gold Ship is in first place!

00:13:19.010 --> 00:13:20.420
And Gold Ship crosses the goal!

00:13:20.420 --> 00:13:25.200
Maiden Charm was just edged out by Gold Ship!

00:13:22.500 --> 00:13:25.200
Gold Ship

00:13:26.720 --> 00:13:28.700
Tennoushou (Spring)

00:13:28.700 --> 00:13:31.700
Tennoushou (Spring)

00:14:14.830 --> 00:14:20.120
The horse girls have all entered the
gate, but only one can emerge victorious.

00:14:20.750 --> 00:14:22.080
It all comes down to this.

00:14:23.610 --> 00:14:25.500
And they're off!

00:14:26.770 --> 00:14:28.680
We're looking at a struggle
for first place already.

00:14:28.680 --> 00:14:31.100
Tudor Garden is currently in the lead.

00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:33.110
Kitasan Black is in second
after a good start!

00:14:33.110 --> 00:14:36.360
And on the outside is Great
House, on the inside, Xbalanque,

00:14:36.360 --> 00:14:38.690
along with Cheval Grand and Two-And-Lonely.

00:14:39.050 --> 00:14:40.120
The other of our star competitors,

00:14:40.120 --> 00:14:43.130
second-favored Satono Diamond, is
starting out in the middle of the pack.

00:14:43.130 --> 00:14:46.460
Will this be her third G1 win
following the Arima Kinen?

00:14:46.460 --> 00:14:48.950
She's starting out by observing
the shape of the race.

00:14:51.430 --> 00:14:54.370
They're now rounding the fourth corner
and entering the first home stretch!

00:14:54.670 --> 00:14:56.990
In first place, Tudor Garden is
still maintaining a big lead,

00:14:56.990 --> 00:14:59.120
with Kitasan Black in second!

00:14:59.120 --> 00:15:03.630
And they've just hit the first 1,000 meters
with a time of 58.3 seconds!

00:15:05.630 --> 00:15:09.320
She's actually trying to
outrun Kitasan. But...

00:15:09.320 --> 00:15:13.340
Right. Kitasan's not letting it distract
her and is maintaining a good position.

00:15:13.340 --> 00:15:16.390
She's really acting like
a defending champion!

00:15:16.690 --> 00:15:19.640
Tudor Garden is continuing
at a noticeably high pace!

00:15:19.640 --> 00:15:21.650
Her lead looks to be about
six to seven lengths!

00:15:22.200 --> 00:15:26.400
I'm not gonna get distracted.
I'm stronger than I was last year,

00:15:26.400 --> 00:15:30.900
so I know I can catch up. And that
means focusing on my own running!

00:15:31.370 --> 00:15:35.830
Tudor Garden rounds the second corner,
with Kitasan Black and Great House in pursuit.

00:15:35.830 --> 00:15:39.410
Cheval Grand, Xbalanque,
and Satono Diamond are behind them.

00:15:39.410 --> 00:15:41.670
This isn't the place to start the fight.

00:15:41.930 --> 00:15:43.460
Right before the third corner...

00:15:43.460 --> 00:15:44.610
The Kyoto hill.

00:15:44.610 --> 00:15:46.610
That'll be when the race picks up.

00:15:46.610 --> 00:15:47.600
Rounding the second corner,

00:15:47.600 --> 00:15:49.540
the runners are moving across
the opposite side of the course.

00:15:49.540 --> 00:15:53.550
Second place is Kitasan Black, with
Great House and Cheval Grand behind her!

00:15:53.550 --> 00:15:54.970
Where will the sparks start to fly?

00:15:54.970 --> 00:15:57.850
Satono Diamond is preserving
her strength in the middle.

00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:02.110
And Tudor Garden is still on the run!
How far will she be able to go?

00:16:09.190 --> 00:16:10.010
Now!

00:16:11.570 --> 00:16:14.810
Oh, and Tudor Garden
slows down on the hill!

00:16:15.450 --> 00:16:18.620
And without skipping a beat,
Satono Diamond starts moving up!

00:16:18.620 --> 00:16:21.820
Tudor Garden's lead is starting to shrink...

00:16:25.050 --> 00:16:28.200
And now Kitasan Black is in the lead!

00:16:28.200 --> 00:16:31.980
And it looks like Satono Diamond is
moving up with the lead in her sights!

00:16:32.350 --> 00:16:34.550
Easy... not yet...

00:16:34.550 --> 00:16:37.550
These 17 horse girls are
faced with massive cheers!

00:16:37.550 --> 00:16:40.310
I'll finish it in the straightâ€”
like at the Arima Kinen!

00:16:41.040 --> 00:16:42.660
And now they're going
around the final corner!

00:16:42.660 --> 00:16:44.190
Kitasan Black is still in the lead!

00:16:44.190 --> 00:16:46.560
She's got a two-length lead that
could mean a consecutive win!

00:16:46.560 --> 00:16:47.810
It's on!

00:16:48.150 --> 00:16:50.070
I am going to win!

00:16:50.070 --> 00:16:53.090
And in the final straight,
they begin their last spurt!

00:16:53.590 --> 00:16:58.190
Kitasan Black is in the lead! But Satono
Diamond is accelerating after her!

00:16:58.190 --> 00:17:00.330
Cheval Grand is closing in as well!

00:17:00.330 --> 00:17:01.690
Do it, Kitasan!

00:17:01.690 --> 00:17:03.460
Leave 'em behind!

00:17:13.620 --> 00:17:15.260
This is where I win it.

00:17:15.260 --> 00:17:17.280
I'll catch up... and pass her!

00:17:49.630 --> 00:17:51.360
R-Remarkable...

00:17:51.360 --> 00:17:53.290
After running in front
for nearly 3,000 meters,

00:17:53.290 --> 00:17:54.840
she's picked up her pace even further!

00:17:54.840 --> 00:17:55.720
Go!

00:17:55.720 --> 00:17:57.330
Her highly-trained body!

00:17:57.330 --> 00:17:59.340
Her keenly-honed spirit!

00:17:58.550 --> 00:17:59.340
Go!

00:17:59.340 --> 00:18:00.350
Go!

00:17:59.340 --> 00:18:01.510
And all of her diligent efforts!

00:18:01.510 --> 00:18:05.210
They propel her across the ground,
as she leaves her pursuers behind!

00:18:08.480 --> 00:18:12.800
Kitasan Black in the lead!

00:18:14.080 --> 00:18:17.200
Kitasan Black barrels toward
the goal amid massive cheers!

00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:18.950
Satono Diamond is looking to pass!

00:18:18.950 --> 00:18:23.120
I don't want to lose! I have
to catch up! It's not over yet!

00:18:34.940 --> 00:18:36.580
Come on, Dia-chan!

00:18:48.540 --> 00:18:50.730
Kita...chan...

00:18:51.510 --> 00:18:52.560
No one...

00:18:52.560 --> 00:18:54.330
No one can catch up!

00:18:54.330 --> 00:18:58.930
With absolutely no one able to reach
her position, she blazes onward in first!

00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:03.070
Kitasan Black's running can only
be described as astonishing!

00:19:03.070 --> 00:19:06.120
With 16 horse girls at her back,
she maintains a champion's dignity!

00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:09.160
Kitasan Black crosses the goal!

00:19:11.500 --> 00:19:16.500
Kitasan Black has won a second
consecutive Spring Tennoushou!

00:19:16.500 --> 00:19:20.760
Not only has she followed up on her
previous performance, she has outdone it!

00:19:20.760 --> 00:19:25.560
The Spring plaque returns
to the champion's possession!

00:19:25.560 --> 00:19:28.900
The second place runner, Cheval Grand,
showed impressive acceleration!

00:19:28.900 --> 00:19:31.520
And Satono Diamond ended up in third.

00:19:31.520 --> 00:19:33.690
This race was considered
a clash of titans,

00:19:33.690 --> 00:19:38.000
and Kitasan Black has done an incredible job
of avenging her loss at the Arima Kinen!

00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:43.200
Hell yeah! That's my apprentice for you!

00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:45.790
They both did great.

00:19:46.320 --> 00:19:47.220
Yes.

00:19:49.760 --> 00:19:51.000
And look at this!

00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:53.860
The winning time was 3:12.5!

00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:54.500
Time

00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:54.500
Record

00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:55.490
That's a new record!

00:19:55.490 --> 00:19:57.500
A shocking accomplishment

00:19:57.500 --> 00:20:00.960
that has stood the test of ten
years has finally been surpassed!

00:20:00.960 --> 00:20:05.120
Kitasan Black has lived up to
her favored status with the fans,

00:20:05.120 --> 00:20:06.700
and won her fifth G1 victory!

00:20:06.700 --> 00:20:08.170
And with a new record to boot!

00:20:08.170 --> 00:20:13.020
There's no doubt she's carved her
name into horse girl history!

00:20:10.020 --> 00:20:11.520
She did it!

00:20:13.450 --> 00:20:15.520
Are you kidding me?

00:20:17.520 --> 00:20:19.530
That was a crazy race.

00:20:19.530 --> 00:20:24.030
Her placing improved from last year.
That's a clear sign of growth.

00:20:25.050 --> 00:20:28.190
You can be proud of how you ran.

00:20:33.740 --> 00:20:37.910
Everyone's smiling... They're so happy.

00:20:38.910 --> 00:20:41.950
From the third corner on, you were
in the lead the whole time.

00:20:42.730 --> 00:20:46.900
From the opening, to the struggle
for positions, and the last spurt...

00:20:46.900 --> 00:20:48.820
It was all perfect.

00:20:51.040 --> 00:20:53.130
You really got me, Kita-chan.

00:20:53.940 --> 00:20:56.010
Congratulations on your win.

00:20:56.650 --> 00:20:59.420
Dia-chan... thank you.

00:21:00.540 --> 00:21:06.230
You always run on ahead of me, showing me
sights that I've never seen before.

00:21:07.120 --> 00:21:08.140
But...

00:21:13.060 --> 00:21:14.910
I guess we're 1-1 now.

00:21:15.800 --> 00:21:17.450
I'm not losing again.

00:21:17.450 --> 00:21:20.460
